tori paitan.review:
Mensho Tokyo opens its doors at 5:00pm from Tuesday to Sunday. I strongly recommend coming early enough to make the first wave of seating. Otherwise, be prepared to stand in line for a couple hours. My roommate and I arrived at 4:30pm and there were already 15 people in the queue. Within the next 5 minutes, another 10 showed up. The small restaurant only seats around 25, so we actually just barely made it.

Worth the hype? Unequivocally.

// Tori Paitan Ramen, Double Chashu ($18) - 5 stars
Mensho's signature dish is the Bay Area's best rendition of the classic tori paitan. The chicken broth was rich and creamy as it should be. The chashu was so tender that even chopsticks could easily tear it apart. The noodles were cooked al dente and had a great bite to them. This was just perfect.

// 1st Anniversary Limited Ramen, Duck & Truffle ($35) - 5 stars
The most delicious bowl of ramen I've ever tasted. They are only preparing 10 servings per day for a limited time. You absolutely have to try this if it's still on the menu. The fragrance of the freshly shaved black truffles mixed into the duck broth was tantalizing, and every spoonful brought out the biggest smile on my face.

